- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on audio data and speech recognition models, which falls under the sound category.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses data protection regulations and proposes a method to check unauthorized use of audio data, which falls under the security category.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with speech recognition models and their training datasets, which falls under the language category.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses data protection regulations and their implications for voice services, which falls under the society category.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method to audit speech recognition models, which falls under the machine learning category.
